FBIS3-59003 "drweu017_a_94002" FBIS-WEU-94-017 Document Type:Daily Report 26 Jan 1994 AUSTRIA Citizens Submit Compensation Claims to Westinghouse AU2501153194 Vienna DER STANDARD in German 25 Jan 94 p 4 AU2501153194 Vienna DER STANDARD Language: German Article Type:BFN [Unattributed report: "Wave of Claims on Temelin Construction Company"] [Text] Salzburg -- Some 90,000 Austrians have submitted compensation claims to the U.S. company Westinghouse -- builder of the Temelin nuclear power plant -- payable in the event of an accident affecting Austria. This has been reported by the nonparty platform against nuclear threats in Salzburg. The demands amount to a total of almost 3 trillion Austrian schillings.
